	\caption{(a) Average current $j/J$ in the center of a system \eqref{eq:sourcedrain} of width 200 sites at times $tJ\sim 10^4$. At $\gamma_c/J \sim 1$ the current is suppressed due to the quantum Zeno effect. In (b) slices through the phase diagram at different driving strengths are shown. Parameters used are $U/J=4,\Delta/J = 2$.}
